{"title":"“Have a Nice Ride” with the New Paul Comp Klamper Stem Top Cap","link":"https://bikerumor.com/have-a-nice-ride-new-paul-comp-klamper-stem-top-cap/","date":1709308800000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-hero-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>More fun goodies from Chico, California’s <a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Paul Components</a>. When you sit and chat with like-minded people, good ideas are bound to spring forth. Like discovering a clever adaptation for a brake caliper part to be used as a stem cap. That’s right, introducing the new Klamper<a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/shop/service-parts/stem-parts/klopcap/\" target=\"_blank\"> Stem Top Cap</a>, </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-the-gang-e1709259056796.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-the-gang.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap the gang\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When a few of the Paul Crüe were taking a second to contemplate the world’s problems, they noticed a Klamper pad adjuster sitting in a box for the steerer-clamp part of the Boxcar Stem. It takes the mind of a bike nerd to take that pad adjuster put it on the stem clamp and think “Hey, this looks cool”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap polished\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-polished-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap machined\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m not sayin’ it doesn’t look cool, I think the new Klamper Stem Top cap completes the aesthetic of the Box Car Stem like it wasn’t an afterthought. I mean, really, nice job team! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s to the bike nerds! </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Obsessively Engineered</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap machined perfectly\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-machined-perfectly-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up-.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap blue close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up-.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-blue-close-up--768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new stem top cap isn’t “actually” a Klamper pad adjuster. It is a precisely machined stem cap that <em>looks</em> like a Klamper pad adjuster. It will fit on any stem/spacer application. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap on the Masi\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-on-the-Masi-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle) On my Masi Incanto</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap On the Gus close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-On-the-Gus-close-up-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle) On my Gus Boots Willsen</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And like it’s always done over at Paul Components, it is machined to tolerances that are “way beyond what a top cap needs”. It’s just what they do over there. It’s like their stuff is going to the moon, or somethin’. I like it. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors.jpeg\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap all the colors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors.jpeg 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors-240x300.jpeg 240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors-800x1000.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors-96x120.jpeg 96w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-all-the-colors-768x960.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Travis said that “We machined <em>Have A Nice Ride</em> on the there because we really want you to have a nice ride”. Nice people over there at Paul Comp.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Components Klamper Stem Top Cap Blue\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Paul-Components-Klamper-Stem-Top-Cap-Blue-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle) On my Masi Incanto</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Klamper Stem Top Cap Tech Info and Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $25 (anodized colors), $40 (polished)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Material: 6061 American-Milled Aluminum</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cap Weight: 6g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Finish: Anodized or Polished</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Anodized colors: Black, Purple, Silver, Pewter, Gold, Blue, Orange, Red, Green, and Pink</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stainless bolt included (no star-nut included)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Machined in Chico, California</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s so much more fun bling and stuff for your trusty bike at the link below. Enjoy!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">PaulComp.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/have-a-nice-ride-new-paul-comp-klamper-stem-top-cap/\">“Have a Nice Ride” with the New Paul Comp Klamper Stem Top Cap</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d300173e72c3ae3a1b41605d88796352f069e99305e3fcf27cf9762f67348e15","category":"Cycling"}